250 g Ground Pork
2 unit(s) Artisan Bun
4 tbsp BBQ Sauce
¼ cup Cheddar Cheese, shredded
285 g Cauliflower
4 tbsp Italian Breadcrumbs
28 g Spring Mix
4 g Garlic Salt
2 tbsp Mayonnaise
1.33 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Before starting, preheat the oven to 450°F.
Wash and dry all produce.
Cut cauliflower into bite-sized pieces.
To a parchment-lined baking sheet, add cauliflower, 1/2 tsp (1 tsp) garlic salt and 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil. Season with pepper, then toss to combine. Roast in the middle of the oven for 7-8 min, until beginning to soften.

Meanwhile, to a small bowl, add cheddar cheese and half the breadcrumbs. Stir to combine. Set aside.
T o a medium bowl, add pork, remaining breadcrumbs and 1/2 tsp (1 tsp) garlic salt. Season with pepper, then combine.
Form mixture into two (four) 4-inch-wide patties.

In a large non-stick pan, heat 1 tsp (2 tsp) oil over medium-high. When the pan is hot, add patties. Cook for 3-5 min per side, until cooked through.** (NOTE: Don't crowd the pan; cook patties in 2 batches for 4 servings, using 1 tsp oil per batch.)
Transfer patties to another medium bowl. Pour BBQ sauce over top, then gently toss to coat. Cover to keep warm.
Meanwhile, flip cauliflower and sprinkle over breadcrumb-cheese mixture. Roast in the middle of the oven for 7-8 min, until cauliflower is tender and cheese is melted.

Halve buns.
On another parchment-lined baking sheet, arrange buns, cut-side up.
Toast buns in the top of the oven for 3-4 min, until golden. (TIP: Keep an eye on them so they don't burn!)

Spread mayo over cut sides of buns.
Top each bottom bun with BBQ pork patties. Drizzle over any remaining sauce from the bowl.
Top with spring mix and close with top bun.
Divide burgers and cheesy cauliflower between plates.